    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Distinctive fortified towers associated with civic buildings in northern Europe. Examples are towers at town halls or market halls, often housing bells and a clock, in Belgium and northern France. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
